[[ch08-overview-metaverse]]
== Overview: Metaverse

New Democracy is a metaverse. New Democracy is an experimental culture where all public works are evaluated as experiments. Experiments require laboratories. These laboratories produce metadata; results about whether the experiment succeeded or failed. The laboratory is a meta process for creating metadata, a metaverse.

It's been in the news recently that Facebook is shutting down its $77 billion virtual reality project called  Metaverse. At the time the Metaverse was first announced I thought that this was a strange choice of branding. This is because the word "meta" came to popular consciousness via Edward Snowden. Snowden revealed a massive surveillance project, PRISM, that collected metadata on all Americans. The US Government is spying on all citizens without a warrant. The US Government pushed back saying that metadata was not owned by any citizen and thereafter usage of the word "meta" took off.

In Dungeons & Dragons we call what the US Government is doing being lawful evil. This is defined as following the letter of the law, but not the spirit of the law. One can say with absolute certainty that the people who wrote the US Constitution would have included metadata, data about data, if they had been aware of it.

So it always seemed odd to me that Facebook branded its virtual reality as "meta". A word made popular by a 1984, Orwellian spying project PRISM. Evil. Branding a product as evil is weird.

As Benjamin Franklin said, those who would give up a little freedom for security and safety deserve neither. We Americans gave up our metadata for security and safety and now deserve neither safety or security.

Meta in software engineering does not just refer to data about data like the phone numbers and IP addresses of Internet messaging. Meta also means any process used to create and collect the metadata in the first place.

For example, Internet logs of log data recording all the URLs that visits a site are metadata. The logging software application is a meta application.

I bring all this up because New Democracy is meta, it doesn't provide direct solutions to problems even though I "tongue in cheek" claim "I have all the solutions(tm)."

New Democracy is a laboratory. A laboratory can be thought of as a meta process. The laboratory defines the experiment, runs the experiment and then results of the experiment are recorded. The laboratory is where the experiment is conducted. In other words a laboratory is a metaverse. It is an artificial setting to collect metadata about experiments in order to determine if the experiment proves some hypothesis correct.

New Democracy is a new laboratory of culture experiments. We can now seek out new solutions to formidable problems today that have no opportunities for solutions because our culture is stagnate.

For example, recently CNN provided investigative reporting that upwards of 62 million American men are learning, promoting, and reinforcing r*pe culture online. Those of us who have been studying r*pe for decades have been aware of these large r*pe statistics for decades. They are not new. The only thing new is the use of online videos.

* 80%-90% of r*pes go unreported
* 60% of r*pes are committed by someone known to the victim
* 98% of reported r*pists walk free


The stats in this reporting go back to the 70s. These stats are staggering to think about. If 98% of r*pists go free where only a tiny 10% are reported then only a tiny percent of r*pes get convicted. In other words, our prisoner system only reports "violent offenders" if r*pe statistics are left out. It is not uncommon to see headlines like "violent crime is down 20%". This is only possible if r*pe is left out. In other words the 90% never reported. 

This is known as a defeatist attitude. I'm a Christian. I think the world is going to end tomorrow, therefore I make no plans for tomorrow. Climate change is destroying humanity. Addressing climate changes requires plans for tomorrow. By not having plans for tomorrow then I will eventually prove I'm right. The world ends.

But it is not just r*pe and sexual assault that is being denied justice.

* 99% of people in prison are there on plea deals, no trials
* 99.9% of civil actions are arbitration,  no trials.

Our culture's "justice" is not justice, it is arbitrary. Plea deals are not justice. Arbitration has the word "arbitrary" built into it. It is not justice. We have massive justice problems with seemingly no avenue or opportunities for improvement. We have no person suggesting solutions for any of this. This is because we need an environment for providing opportunities to find solutions. We need a laboratory. We need experiments to determine the best way to change culture. However...

Old Democracy doesn't scale, it doesn't work as population size increases because it can't adapt to growth. We are stuck, We are fixed in place, sinking in the quicksand of disintegrating society. A society that is insane. Insanity is doing the same thing over and over again even as we grow. We are stuck on the insanity of playing musical chairs where politicians circle around and when the bell sounds, we vote in a politician to fix things. They aren't fixing anything.

Are there solutions though? Religion would have us think things will always be the same. And yet...some native American tribes would sleep as a tribe in a big tent. Oh the snoring! Shiver :) Still, one has to wonder if differences in cultural behavior like this would improve behavior towards women? We won't ever know unless we free our minds, free ourselves from our mental slavery.

Our mental slavery is best described as western culture slavery brought on by capitalist stagnation. Capitalism profits the most by selling everyone the same thing, the same culture. Like Coke. Capitalist cultures stagnate, they do not adapt. This is due to continuously selling us the past as the present without change in order to maximize profit. If not for our culture being obsessed with continuously adopting new technology then our culture would be stuck drinking Coke forever. Fini.

Today, New Democracy has no immediate solutions to our intractable Old Democracy problems like violence against women. That's because we don't know the solutions. Rather, New Democracy is a metaverse, an experimental culture. MGOs of fixed size 30 people are the nations. 300 million nations is an experimental culture.

First off, New Democracy removes old stagnate culture blocks:
* No nations
* No hierarchy
* No capitalism
* No currency, just direct trade
* No land private property

We must remove these blocks. If we are afraid of change then we are perfect capitalist captives, perfect capitalist market, and perfect capitalist slaves. We must embrace change. If not? Well...in the TV series Firefly, a perfection of capitalism is depicted:

One nation. 

In Firefly the final nations merging were China and the US. The final nation is called "The Alliance". That's our future. Stagnate. Everything is the same. Pure profit of least products. Don't get me wrong, the capitalists will always be at war. However, illusion will be sold to us as change. Brands. Colors. Logos. These will satisfy as differences for us to preen about as is our individual nature. To be individuals.

Capitalism isn't our only large culture problem. We also need to address the elephant in the room: religion. Religion is a fixed culture and there is nothing more to say. Religion and capitalism make a perfect couple. Husband and wife.  Why? Stagnate culture. Fixed society. Diversity is the enemy of profits and religion.  Slight diversity within White Christian Nationalism culture is a match made in heaven between capitalism and religion.

New Democracy doesn't address religion per se. That's because unlike capitalism, religion is broadly defined. We will have to tackle managing religion one day at a time.

And time is of the essence.  Our window of time to eliminate capitalist tyranny is closing fast. By contrast, regrouping as a new culture will need many generations. Once the rich get their hands on indefinite lifespans and other genetic engineering advances that they reserve to themselves, then it will be game over.

New Democracy is a new culture laboratory, or metaverse. There are 300 million micro-nations as our laboratory equipment. They can be combined and isolated depending on the experiment hypothesis. 
We do have Old Democracy  ideas to use as hypothesis for New Democracy experiments today. Inventing New Democracy has meant studying sociology since the 1980s. Here are some Old Democracy  r*pe hypothesis threads to pull:1. R*pe is violence. Solve violence, solve r*pe. 
2. Religion makes masterb****n bad. Make masterb****n  good.
3. Testosterone levels. Violence in males subside with age.

We have no Old Democracy avenues of opportunity to study those hypotheses today. We can't treat nations as part of some experiment control. Heck, we can't even treat States within the US as experiment controls. New Democracy is designed from the ground up as a new permanent laboratory of moving away from trial-and-error evolution to trial-and-error science.

New Democracy is spying. Or, rather, monitoring. Experiments need metadata. New Democracy requires everyone to have Internet access and a smartphone. MGO members are required to input data daily about what was eaten, exercise taken, sleep information and so on. This is the only way science works, observation.

New Democracy is also meta in that it requires billions if not trillions of new sensors to be deployed all over Earth. New Democracy requires an Earth AI. This Earth AI will use these billions of sensors for temperatures, soil, wind, rain and other data to simulate new projects. If we are going to manage climate on Earth well into the future, then we need permanent whole Earth AI simulation for all large scale Earth impacting projects.

New Democracy is also meta in that it is a virtual reality similar to Facebook's Metaverse. The Earth AI for Earth simulation is real time and real data only. There is no fabrication. However, the VERY, or "virtual Earth, reality you", is a clone of the Earth AI. It is real Earth with you moving around it. It requires every MGO to have a camera room. This room will have projectors for walls, ceiling and floor. The people in the room are given coordinates as a room with the VERY. People are projected as they actually appear. This VERY allows for people to meet and communicate with anyone else on Earth without the time and resources required to travel. We just teleport. Unless you wanna walk. :)

New Democracy has all the solutions(tm). New Democracy has all the solutions not because it has the solutions, but because it is the laboratory required to experiment on all the solutions indefinitely. New Democracy is a permanent culture of forever experimenting in order to adapt to our Universe indefinitely.

New Democracy provides meta solutions using meta monitoring and meta virtual reality.

New Democracy is a metaverse culture and thus requires high tech to create its culture.

Welcome to the actual metaverse.



